Hemispermatophore (Figs: 41-k): Lamelliform (TL: 3.6; LL: 1.2; LW: 
0.8 mm
); lamella straight, as wide as capsule and with small apical crest; hook short, basal, with two small, pointed denticles. Capsule with median lobe entally.
